CHELSEA legend Petr Cech has backed goalkeeper Edouard Mendy to guide Senegal to their first-ever Africa Cup of Nations title in Cameroon. The Lions of Teranga reached the quarter-finals of the competition after beating Cape Verde 2-0 in the Round of 16 with Liverpool forward Sadio Mane and Bamba Dieng of Ligue 1 club Marseille notching the goals at Stade Omnisports de Bafoussam. Read Also: Rooney: Why I turned down Everton manager’s job   Rooney: Why I turned down Everton manager’s job     Mukairu excited after ₦900m move to FC Copenhagen     Iheanacho: my unforgettable AFCON partnership with Awoniyi   Writing in his weekly column, Cech suggested the 29-year-old custodian, who recently won the Fifa Best goalkeeper award, will win more trophies this year among them the Afcon title as Senegal are among the favourites. “Edou was named The Best goalkeeper by Fifa and it’s another great achievement for him,” Cech wrote on Chelsea’s official website. “He is the first African goalkeeper to win the award, which is amazing, and testament to how well he has done since he came to our club. - Advertisement - “He had an incredible year, winning two trophies, and it reflects his hard work and attitude. It’s great to see him getting recognition and our other players who made it to the Team of the Year.